 Each lung - even a healthy one - tends to collapse. The goal of "The Open Lung Concept" is to reaerate collapsed alveoli and to keep them open. Thus, mechanical ventilation has to aim at recruiting alveoli for gas exchange. This article explains the basics of alveolar physiology and the therapeutic approaches derived from it. In addition, the practical conduct of the alveolar recruitment maneuver is explained for the clinician.  
